snippet.textDisplay:
I think the XT series was meant to hit 2 birds with 1 stone. 

1) Embarrass Intel 10th gen
2) back when AMD was not considering support of the B3xx and B4xx series motherboards on the Zen 3 CPU's, this was to be a consolation for those owenrs. 

The backlash with non support of older Mobo's has changed AMD's plans, so now older gen mobo owners have even more choice once Zen 3 is released. You can go either XT or "customized" BIOS for Zen 3.
snippet.textOriginal:
